tool.summary: Adds the required visibility modifier fields to a point feature class for use in Radial Line Of Sight (RLOS).
tool.usage:
Run this tool on Observers, before running Radial Line of Sight (RLOS).

The Controlling the visibility analysis (http://pro.arcgis.com/en/pro-app/tool-reference/3d-analyst/using-viewshed-and-observer-points-for-visibility.htm) topic discusses the fields added.

Fields added include:

  • OFFSETA: vertical offset added to the observer positions

  • OFFSETB: vertical offset added to surface cells for visibility calculation

  • AZIMUTH1: start (left) angle in horizontal field of view

  • AZIMUTH2: end (right) angle in a horizontal field of view

  • VERT1: top angle in vertical field of view

  • VERT2: bottom angle in vertical field of view

  • RADIUS1: nearest distance from observer to consider for analysis

  • RADIUS2: farthest distance from observer

Units of the heights are the units of the elevation surface; distance units are in the linear units of the coordinate system of the features class.
